---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = "Speech Investigation - Research Methods";
const description = "Details about the speech research investigation methodology.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Navigation slot="navigation" currentPage="investigation" />
  
  <article>
    <Breadcrumb currentPage="Speech Investigation" />

    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Speech Investigation</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Research Methods and Approach</p>
    </header>

    <section class="content">
      <h2>Passive Research Methodology</h2>
      <p>
        Unlike controlled laboratory experiments, our research employs a passive observation 
        methodology. This approach captures natural, spontaneous speech without prompting 
        or artificial stimuli, providing insight into genuine language use.
      </p>

      <h2>Documentation Process</h2>
      <p>
        Each speech event is carefully documented with the following information:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The exact utterance (transcription)</li>
        <li>Audio recording when possible</li>
        <li>Context and environmental factors</li>
        <li>Time and date</li>
        <li>Observer notes on bird behavior</li>
        <li>Any preceding events or interactions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Analysis Framework</h2>
      <p>
        Speech samples are analyzed for several key factors:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Novelty:</strong> Is the utterance original or a direct repetition?</li>
        <li><strong>Context appropriateness:</strong> Does the speech fit the situation?</li>
        <li><strong>Grammatical structure:</strong> Does the bird apply grammar rules?</li>
        <li><strong>Pronoun usage:</strong> Does the bird understand pronouns?</li>
        <li><strong>Verb conjugation:</strong> Are verbs correctly matched to subjects?</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Key Findings</h2>
      <p>
        Our investigation has revealed several significant findings about Arielle's 
        language abilities:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Consistent pronoun substitution (I, you, she)</li>
        <li>Correct verb conjugation to match subjects</li>
        <li>Contextually appropriate vocabulary selection</li>
        <li>Novel combinations of learned phrases</li>
        <li>Emotional tone modulation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Ongoing Research</h2>
      <p>
        This research continues as we document more examples of Arielle's speech. 
        Each new observation adds to our understanding of avian language capabilities 
        and the potential for meaningful interspecies communication.
      </p>
    </section>

    <Footer />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    color: #663300;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: #666;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 750px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .content h2 {
    color: #009966;
    margin-top: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
  }

  .content h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5em;
    color: #333;
  }

  .content ul {
    margin: 20px 0;
    padding-left: 30px;
  }

  .content li {
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .content li strong {
    color: #663300;
  }
</style>
